  "prompt": "What business model does olx use?",
  "response": "OLX primarily uses a classifieds business model. This model allows users to post advertisements for goods and services they want to sell or offer, typically for free or for a nominal fee. The platform generates revenue through various means, including:\n\n1. **Premium Listings**: Users can pay to have their ads highlighted or featured for better visibility, increasing the chances of their items being sold quickly.\n2. **Advertising**: OLX earns revenue from display advertisements on their website and app. Companies pay to reach OLX\u2019s large user base.\n3. **Subscription Services**: Some OLX platforms offer subscription-based services for businesses and professional sellers, providing them with tools and analytics to enhance their selling experience.\n4. **Transaction Fees**: In some regions, OLX might charge a commission or transaction fee for certain types of sales, such as automotive or real estate transactions.\n\nBy leveraging these revenue streams, OLX can provide a marketplace where users can buy and sell items locally and globally.",
